entry.summary:
# Feed Testing

This is an index for the folder that contains a feed.

!!!
${o.feeds.posts.map(post =&gt; {
    return macro('post', {
        title: post.title, 
        content: post.configuration.description
    })
}).join('\n')}
!!!

And here is a second way to write a feed:

!!!
${o.feeds.posts.map(post =&gt; {
    return md(`
# [${post.title}](${post.url})
${post.configuration.description}
`)
}).join('\n')}
!!!

Testing to make sure that HTML inside code tags work, because there was a time that they didn't: 

```
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
        &lt;title&gt;HTML Title&lt;/title&gt;
        &lt;!-- You can add css here. ---&gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;div id="app"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;script src="index.js" inline="inline"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

Testing various css styles

Maybe eventually I'll get at shorthand to work too!

